page.title: 02LISTED BUILDINGS
page.content: The following are the listed buildings in{Moore. {Village Farm}-17 cent.Stone and red brick.Flag roof.Jacobean entrance piers to garden.{Old Hall Farm}18 cent.Brown brick.Converted to two private dwellings.{Old Hall Farm {Cottages}18 cent. Brown brick cottages {Ivy Cottage}18 cent.Brown brick with slate roof.{Manor Farm}17 cent with alterations.Stone with timber frame.Tile roof.Inscription on gable LVNE:X1:1660:EC.{Barn at Manor Farm}18 cent. Brick with slate roof.{Red Lion} 18 cent.Interior evidence of wattle and daub.{The Pebbles}18 cent.Brown brick cottage.{Moore House}18 cent.3 storey brown brick house.Large grounds.{Moore Hall}17 cent.3 storey roughcast house.Slate roof.Large grounds.{Moore Hall Cottage}18 cent red brick former barn.Tile roof.
